## Using a comma ',' in print()

#### When you use commas inside a `print()` statement, Python treats each item as a separate argument. 

#### Here's what that means in simple terms:

- #### Python will automatically convert each item into a string, if it's not already.
- #### Python will also add a space between each item when it prints them.




<p style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #8148B2; display: inline-block;">
